<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
In Greece, this subspecies is reported only from the floristic region of NC Greece, where it occurs on Mt. Voras (also known as Kaimaktsalan) and Mt. Varnous (
<bibRefCitation author="Anagnostopoulos, A." journalOrPublisher="ARG Gantner Verlag KG, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667693" refString="Anagnostopoulos, A., Strid, A., 2002. Flora Hellenica 2. ARG Gantner Verlag KG, Ruggell" title="Flora Hellenica 2" year="2002">Anagnostopoulos and Strid 2002</bibRefCitation>
). This is the third report from Greece (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F7677696" captionText="Figure 22. Saxifraga pedemontana subsp. cymosa from Mt. Rodopi (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640579" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">22</figureCitation>
) and the first one from the floristic region of the NE (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F7677669" captionText="Figure 17. Distribution map of Convolvulus suendermannii, Lomelosia rhodopensis, Drymocallis rupestris and Saxifraga pedemontana subsp. cymosa in Greece." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656581" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
